Chrony NTP server for Home Assistant — synchronize from upstream NTP and serve time on your LAN.

## About

This add-on runs **Chrony** as an NTP server (UDP 123). It is based on the [Community chrony add-on](https://github.com/hassio-addons/addon-chrony) and the former [ha-chronyd](https://github.com/HenryHST/ha-chronyd) project.

## Installation

1. Navigate to **Supervisor** → **Add-on Store**
2. Add repository: `{{ repository }}`
3. Install **Chrony NTP**
4. Start the add-on

## Configuration

```yaml
set_system_clock: true
ntp_pool: pool.ntp.org
ntp_server:
  - de.pool.ntp.org
pool_maxsources: 4
log_level: info
```

See [DOCS.md](DOCS.md) for details and migration notes.

